Φ(Chakra) = σ(insight|intuition) ∘ ρ(emotion|flow) ∘ λ(power|transformation) ∘ β(growth|healing) ∘ δγ(grounding|survival) ∘ μ(alignment|structure) + ε | :integrated_flow

; === Operator Breakdown ===

; σ — Air / Aerunik (0.77)
;   Third Eye (Ajna) and Crown (Sahasrara) chakras. Intuitive insight and
;   spiritual perception beyond the material senses. Aerunik governs the upper
;   two centers where awareness opens into transpersonal dimensions — the Third
;   Eye as inner vision and pattern recognition, the Crown as connection to
;   universal consciousness. These are the most ethereal centers, where individual
;   perception merges with cosmic awareness.

; ρ — Water / Sentaria (0.81)
;   Sacral (Svadhisthana) and Heart (Anahata) chakras. Emotional flow, creative
;   expression, and compassionate connection. Sentaria governs the water-nature
;   of these centers: the Sacral's creative-sexual-emotional fluidity and the
;   Heart's capacity for love that flows without condition. Together they
;   represent the feeling dimension of the chakra system — the capacity to be
;   moved, to create, and to connect through emotional resonance.

; λ — Fire / Jvalion (0.74)
;   Solar Plexus (Manipura) chakra. Personal power, transformative will, and
;   the digestive fire that processes raw experience into usable energy. Jvalion
;   governs the center where individual agency asserts itself — the capacity to
;   act with power, to transform circumstances, and to maintain personal
;   boundaries. Also governs kundalini activation: the ascending fire that
;   opens higher centers when properly channeled.

; β — Wood / Arboriel (0.70)
;   Heart (Anahata) as bridge function. The Heart chakra uniquely bridges lower
;   (survival, emotion, power) and higher (expression, insight, transcendence)
;   centers. Arboriel governs this organic connective growth — the living bridge
;   that allows energy to move between earthly and spiritual domains. Healing
;   growth occurs through the Heart's integrative capacity.

; δγ — Earth / Humavita (0.83)
;   The dominant operator. Root (Muladhara) chakra. Survival instinct, material
;   stability, and embodied grounding. Humavita governs the foundation without
;   which no higher development is possible — the primal connection to earth,
;   body, and physical existence. The chakra system insists that spiritual
;   ascent requires material grounding; the root must be stable before the
;   crown can open safely.

; μ — Metal / Ferrosid (0.66)
;   Throat (Vishuddha) chakra. Structural alignment of inner truth with outer
;   expression. Ferrosid governs the precision required for authentic
;   communication — speaking what is true in a form that can be received.
;   The throat center is the structural gateway: it gives form (sound, word,
;   expression) to formless inner states. Lower emphasis reflects that the
;   system prioritizes flow and grounding over structural articulation.

; === Z-State ===
; Integrated flow — all seven centers open and balanced, energy moving freely
; along the central axis (sushumna). The Z-state is not the dominance of any
; single chakra but their harmonious integration: grounded yet transcendent,
; powerful yet compassionate, expressive yet receptive.

; === Tendency ===
; δγ → 0.83 — The system leans toward grounding (earth). Without root
; stability, all higher development is unstable. The chakra tradition insists
; on building from the ground up: survival before transcendence, embodiment
; before liberation.

# CE-STATE: multiscale
# EI-NOTE: Causal power distributed across multiple description levels
